title: congreso right coalitions

You should not be here? Report a bug if you see this text.

@pp_cs
title: <span style="color: var(--cs); font-style: italic;">Liberal</span> <span style="color: var(--pp); font-style: italic;">Right</span> Coalition (PP - csspa)
subtitle: A PP + csspa cabinet, backed by the centralist-right and other smaller partie. [? if congreso_coalition_pp_cs_talks: It leans on tolerations they'll have to negotiate. ?]
view-if: congreso_coalition_pp_cs_s > congreso_s_majority - 50
choose-if: congreso_coalition_pp_cs_reach
unavailable-subtitle: PP and Cs fall short of investiture, even with the smaller parties they could win over.
on-arrival: {!
    // TODO — form the PP + Cs coalition cabinet.
    //   • president = pp, Cs in government; centralist-right minors support,
    //     pact-pragmatists (cc/prc/te/pnv) abstain, the Catalan right per roadmap.
    //   • the player (Catalan minor) almost always OPPOSES — little to no lever.
!}

