@cs_pp
title: <span style="color: var(--cs); font-style: italic;">Liberal</span> <span style="color: var(--pp); font-style: italic;">Coalition</span> (csspa - PP)
subtitle: A csspa-led cabinet with the PP as the junior partner, backed by the centralist-right and other smaller parties. [? if congreso_coalition_pp_cs_talks: It leans on tolerations they'll have to negotiate. ?]
view-if: congreso_coalition_cs_pp_s > congreso_s_majority - 50
choose-if: congreso_coalition_pp_cs_reach
unavailable-subtitle: Cs and PP fall short of investiture, even with the smaller parties they could win over.
on-arrival: {!
    // TODO — form the Cs-led liberal cabinet (Cs president, PP the junior partner).
    //   • mirrors @pp_cs but with the bigger party (Cs) taking the presidency; the
    //     same right minors back it. Shares congreso_coalition_pp_cs_reach (the
    //     PP+Cs arithmetic is identical — only who-leads differs).
!}

